cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

The paper deals with multi-atlas segmentation in medical image analysis, which is a common problem in computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method involves formulating the problem as a Markov Random Field energy minimization problem, which is a common technique in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also involves experiments on Magnetic Resonance Imaging (MRI) datasets, which is a common application in multimedia (cs.MM) and neural networks (cs.NE).
